#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:2
msgid "Tornado 3.1 新特性"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:5
msgid "Jun 15, 2013"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:8
msgid "Multiple modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:10
msgid ""
"Many reference cycles have been broken up throughout the package, "
"allowing for more efficient garbage collection on CPython."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:12
msgid ""
"Silenced some log messages when connections are opened and immediately "
"closed (i.e. port scans), or other situations related to closed "
"connections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:15
msgid ""
"Various small speedups: `.HTTPHeaders` case normalization, `.UIModule` "
"proxy objects, precompile some regexes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:19
msgid "`tornado.auth`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:21
msgid ""
"`~tornado.auth.OAuthMixin` always sends ``oauth_version=1.0`` in its "
"request as required by the spec."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:23
msgid ""
"`~tornado.auth.FacebookGraphMixin` now uses ``self._FACEBOOK_BASE_URL`` "
"in `~.FacebookGraphMixin.facebook_request` to allow the base url to be "
"overridden."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:26
msgid ""
"The ``authenticate_redirect`` and ``authorize_redirect`` methods in the "
"`tornado.auth` mixin classes all now return Futures.  These methods are "
"asynchronous in `.OAuthMixin` and derived classes, although they do not "
"take a callback.  The `.Future` these methods return must be yielded if "
"they are called from a function decorated with `.gen.coroutine` (but not "
"`.gen.engine`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:32
msgid ""
"`.TwitterMixin` now uses ``/account/verify_credentials`` to get "
"information about the logged-in user, which is more robust against "
"changing screen names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:35
msgid ""
"The ``demos`` directory (in the source distribution) has a new "
"``twitter`` demo using `.TwitterMixin`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:39
msgid "`tornado.escape`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:41
msgid ""
"`.url_escape` and `.url_unescape` have a new ``plus`` argument "
"(defaulting to True for consistency with the previous behavior) which "
"specifies whether they work like `urllib.parse.unquote` or "
"`urllib.parse.unquote_plus`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:46
msgid "`tornado.gen`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:48
msgid ""
"Fixed a potential memory leak with long chains of `tornado.gen` "
"coroutines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:51
msgid "`tornado.httpclient`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:53
msgid ""
"`tornado.httpclient.HTTPRequest` takes a new argument ``auth_mode``, "
"which can be either ``basic`` or ``digest``.  Digest authentication is "
"only supported with ``tornado.curl_httpclient``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:56
msgid ""
"``tornado.curl_httpclient`` no longer goes into an infinite loop when "
"pycurl returns a negative timeout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:58
msgid ""
"``curl_httpclient`` now supports the ``PATCH`` and ``OPTIONS`` methods "
"without the use of ``allow_nonstandard_methods=True``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:60
msgid ""
"Worked around a class of bugs in libcurl that would result in errors from"
" `.IOLoop.update_handler` in various scenarios including digest "
"authentication and socks proxies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:63
msgid ""
"The ``TCP_NODELAY`` flag is now set when appropriate in "
"``simple_httpclient``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:64
msgid ""
"``simple_httpclient`` no longer logs exceptions, since those exceptions "
"are made available to the caller as ``HTTPResponse.error``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:68
msgid "`tornado.httpserver`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:70
msgid ""
"`tornado.httpserver.HTTPServer` handles malformed HTTP headers more "
"gracefully."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:72
msgid ""
"`.HTTPServer` now supports lists of IPs in ``X-Forwarded-For`` (it "
"chooses the last, i.e. nearest one)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:74
msgid ""
"Memory is now reclaimed promptly on CPython when an HTTP request fails "
"because it exceeded the maximum upload size."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:76
msgid "The ``TCP_NODELAY`` flag is now set when appropriate in `.HTTPServer`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:77
msgid ""
"The `.HTTPServer` ``no_keep_alive`` option is now respected with HTTP 1.0"
" connections that explicitly pass ``Connection: keep-alive``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:79
msgid ""
"The ``Connection: keep-alive`` check for HTTP 1.0 connections is now "
"case-insensitive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:81
msgid ""
"The `str` and `repr` of ``tornado.httpserver.HTTPRequest`` no longer "
"include the request body, reducing log spam on errors (and potential "
"exposure/retention of private data)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:86
msgid "`tornado.httputil`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:88
msgid "The cache used in `.HTTPHeaders` will no longer grow without bound."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:91
msgid "`tornado.ioloop`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:93
msgid ""
"Some `.IOLoop` implementations (such as ``pyzmq``) accept objects other "
"than integer file descriptors; these objects will now have their "
"``.close()`` method called when the ``IOLoop` is closed with "
"``all_fds=True``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:97
msgid ""
"The stub handles left behind by `.IOLoop.remove_timeout` will now get "
"cleaned up instead of waiting to expire."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:101
msgid "`tornado.iostream`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:103
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug in `.BaseIOStream.read_until_close` that would sometimes "
"cause data to be passed to the final callback instead of the streaming "
"callback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:106
msgid ""
"The `.IOStream` close callback is now run more reliably if there is an "
"exception in ``_try_inline_read``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:108
msgid ""
"New method `.BaseIOStream.set_nodelay` can be used to set the "
"``TCP_NODELAY`` flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:110
msgid ""
"Fixed a case where errors in ``SSLIOStream.connect`` (and "
"``SimpleAsyncHTTPClient``) were not being reported correctly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:114
msgid "`tornado.locale`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:116
msgid "`.Locale.format_date` now works on Python 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:119
msgid "`tornado.netutil`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:121
msgid "The default `.Resolver` implementation now works on Solaris."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:122
msgid "`.Resolver` now has a `~.Resolver.close` method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:123
msgid ""
"Fixed a potential CPU DoS when ``tornado.netutil.ssl_match_hostname`` is "
"used on certificates with an abusive wildcard pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:125
msgid ""
"All instances of `.ThreadedResolver` now share a single thread pool, "
"whose size is set by the first one to be created (or the static "
"``Resolver.configure`` method)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:128
msgid "`.ExecutorResolver` is now documented for public use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:129
msgid "`.bind_sockets` now works in configurations with incomplete IPv6 support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:132
msgid "`tornado.options`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:134
msgid "`tornado.options.define` with ``multiple=True`` now works on Python 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:135
msgid ""
"`tornado.options.options` and other `.OptionParser` instances support "
"some new dict-like methods: `~.OptionParser.items()`, iteration over "
"keys, and (read-only) access to options with square braket syntax. "
"`.OptionParser.group_dict` returns all options with a given group name, "
"and `.OptionParser.as_dict` returns all options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:142
msgid "`tornado.process`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:144
msgid ""
"`tornado.process.Subprocess` no longer leaks file descriptors into the "
"child process, which fixes a problem in which the child could not detect "
"that the parent process had closed its stdin pipe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:147
msgid ""
"`.Subprocess.set_exit_callback` now works for subprocesses created "
"without an explicit ``io_loop`` parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:151
msgid "`tornado.stack_context`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:153
msgid "`tornado.stack_context` has been rewritten and is now much faster."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:154
msgid ""
"New function `.run_with_stack_context` facilitates the use of stack "
"contexts with coroutines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:158
msgid "`tornado.tcpserver`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:160
msgid ""
"The constructors of `.TCPServer` and `.HTTPServer` now take a "
"``max_buffer_size`` keyword argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:164
msgid "`tornado.template`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:166
msgid ""
"Some internal names used by the template system have been changed; now "
"all \"reserved\" names in templates start with ``_tt_``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:170
msgid "`tornado.testing`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:172
msgid ""
"`tornado.testing.AsyncTestCase.wait` now raises the correct exception "
"when it has been modified by `tornado.stack_context`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:174
msgid ""
"`tornado.testing.gen_test` can now be called as ``@gen_test(timeout=60)``"
" to give some tests a longer timeout than others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:176
msgid ""
"The environment variable ``ASYNC_TEST_TIMEOUT`` can now be set to "
"override the default timeout for `.AsyncTestCase.wait` and `.gen_test`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:178
msgid ""
"`.bind_unused_port` now passes ``None`` instead of ``0`` as the port to "
"``getaddrinfo``, which works better with some unusual network "
"configurations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:183
msgid "`tornado.util`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:185
msgid ""
"`tornado.util.import_object` now works with top-level module names that "
"do not contain a dot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:187
msgid ""
"`tornado.util.import_object` now consistently raises `ImportError` "
"instead of `AttributeError` when it fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:191
msgid "`tornado.web`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:193
msgid ""
"The ``handlers`` list passed to the `tornado.web.Application` constructor"
" and `~tornado.web.Application.add_handlers` methods can now contain "
"lists in addition to tuples and `~tornado.web.URLSpec` objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:196
msgid ""
"`tornado.web.StaticFileHandler` now works on Windows when the client "
"passes an ``If-Modified-Since`` timestamp before 1970."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:198
msgid ""
"New method `.RequestHandler.log_exception` can be overridden to customize"
" the logging behavior when an exception is uncaught.  Most apps that "
"currently override ``_handle_request_exception`` can now use a "
"combination of `.RequestHandler.log_exception` and `.write_error`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:203
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.get_argument` now raises `.MissingArgumentError` (a "
"subclass of `tornado.web.HTTPError`, which is what it raised previously) "
"if the argument cannot be found."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:206
msgid ""
"`.Application.reverse_url` now uses `.url_escape` with ``plus=False``, "
"i.e. spaces are encoded as ``%20`` instead of ``+``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:208
msgid ""
"Arguments extracted from the url path are now decoded with "
"`.url_unescape` with ``plus=False``, so plus signs are left as-is instead"
" of being turned into spaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:211
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.send_error` will now only be called once per request, "
"even if multiple exceptions are caught by the stack context."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:213
msgid ""
"The `tornado.web.asynchronous` decorator is no longer necessary for "
"methods that return a `.Future` (i.e. those that use the `.gen.coroutine`"
" or `.return_future` decorators)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:216
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.prepare` may now be asynchronous if it returns a "
"`.Future`.  The `~tornado.web.asynchronous` decorator is not used with "
"``prepare``; one of the `.Future`-related decorators should be used "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:219
msgid "``RequestHandler.current_user`` may now be assigned to normally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:220
msgid ""
"`.RequestHandler.redirect` no longer silently strips control characters "
"and whitespace.  It is now an error to pass control characters, newlines "
"or tabs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:223
msgid ""
"`.StaticFileHandler` has been reorganized internally and now has "
"additional extension points that can be overridden in subclasses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:225
msgid ""
"`.StaticFileHandler` now supports HTTP ``Range`` requests. "
"`.StaticFileHandler` is still not suitable for files too large to "
"comfortably fit in memory, but ``Range`` support is necessary in some "
"browsers to enable seeking of HTML5 audio and video."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:229
msgid ""
"`.StaticFileHandler` now uses longer hashes by default, and uses the same"
" hashes for ``Etag`` as it does for versioned urls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:231
msgid ""
"`.StaticFileHandler.make_static_url` and `.RequestHandler.static_url` now"
" have an additional keyword argument ``include_version`` to suppress the "
"url versioning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:234
msgid ""
"`.StaticFileHandler` now reads its file in chunks, which will reduce "
"memory fragmentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:236
msgid ""
"Fixed a problem with the ``Date`` header and cookie expiration dates when"
" the system locale is set to a non-english configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:240
msgid "`tornado.websocket`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:242
msgid ""
"`.WebSocketHandler` now catches `.StreamClosedError` and runs "
"`~.WebSocketHandler.on_close` immediately instead of logging a stack "
"trace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:245
msgid ""
"New method `.WebSocketHandler.set_nodelay` can be used to set the "
"``TCP_NODELAY`` flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:249
msgid "`tornado.wsgi`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../releases/v3.1.0.rst:251
msgid ""
"Fixed an exception in `.WSGIContainer` when the connection is closed "
"while output is being written."
msgstr ""

